choices.text:
Put together a healthy meal plan for me for today presuming no dietary restrictions.
Sure, here is an example of what I think would be a good and balanced diet.  It includes foods from all the food groups to ensure you are getting enough nutrients in your daily meals. 
Breakfast - 1 cup oatmeal with blueberries; 2 slices whole wheat bread with almond butter and banana lunch- 3 oz chicken breast, brown rice, steamed broccoli dinner – 4 oz salmon filet, quinoa, asparagus
